copy of the Extra Judicial Settlement of Estate of the deceased Floresma Alivia- Dacuycuy;
Applicable BIR Zonal Value;
Deed of Absolute Sale registered with the Register of Deeds where the land is located;
Certified Photocopy of Tax Clearance from Assessor’s Office where the land is located;
Certificate Authorizing Registration (CAR);
Proof of payment of Capital Gains Tax (CGT);
Proof of payment of Documentary Stamp Tax (DST);
Proof of payment of Transfer Tax; and
duly approved subdivision plan, since the lot acquired by the Municipality is part of an undivided portion of a parcel of land.

We recommended the Management submit:
justification on the basis of arriving of the purchase price of the three (3) lots and the non-availment of the services of an independent appraiser for the determination of the current market value of the land pursuant to Section 13.1 of COA Circular 2012-001 dated June 12, 2012 and Section 6 of the IRR of RA No. 10752;
valid proof of negotiation conducted by the Municipality and the owner of the land in order for the Audit Team to determine how the purchase price was arrived;
